deck: "Home of The Private Eye digital comicbook by Brian K. Vaughan, Marcos Martin and Muntsa Vicente and Universe! by Albert Monteys."
description:
Panel Syndicate is a unique pay-what-you-want and DRM-free digital comic publisher created by artist Marcos Martin and writer Brian K. Vaughan where they publish creator owned books and with no set price. Buyers can purchase issues from them for whatever price they would like to pay and the payment goes directly to the author's Paypal account.

The first comic published by Panel Syndicate was The Private Eye, in March 2013. Their second comic, UNIVERSE! - The Periodical of Cosmic Wonders, was published in November 2014.

All comics books are published in English and Spanish and occasionally in Catalan, Portuguese, and French.
name: Panelsyndicate

description: Born in Amsterdam, Netherlands, Arnold and Jacob Pander, are critically acclaimed graphic novelists and award winning filmmakers with a history of work in the popular arts and media. The collaborative sibling duo has created a number of graphic novels and comics for Image, Marvel, Dark Horse, and DC Comics. The brothers’ fashion forward art and cinematic eye first appeared in the break out indie series, Grendel: Devil’s Legacy. Nominated for the Eisner and Manning awards for groundbreaking artwork in the comics medium, the Pander Bros. embarked on a 20 year career in comics, creating a wide range of original comics and graphic novels including; The Dissident (formerly XXX), Secret Broadcast, Accelerate, Batman: City of Light, and more. The Pander Brothers distinct visual style and unique collaborations with some of the industries’ top writers, has solidified them as a major creative force in the graphic novel medium.
name: Pander Bros Comics

deck: Comic imprint created in 2013 by Titan Magazines
description:
Originally comics were printed under the Titan Magazines and trades under Titan Books. In 2013 Titan created the comics imprint to publish original creator-owned comics alongside new and classic graphic novels!

The imprint will launch in July 2013 with two creator-owned miniseries and four new collections, with a new series beginning each month afterwards:

  • Chronos Commandos: Dawn Patrol by writer/artist Stuart Jennett (Marvel UK)
  • Numbercruncher by X-Men: Legacy writer Si Spurrier and 2000AD artist P.J. Holden
  • Ring of Roses – collected in color for the first time, by writer Das Petrou and artist John Watkiss
  • Thrud The Barbarian by writer/artist Carl Critchlow (2000AD, Magic: The Gathering)
  • The First Kingdom by comic legend Jack Katz

The second wave will see three new series launching later in the year:

September

  • Gravestown by writer Roger Gibson and artist Vince Danks (Harker)
  • Surface Tension by writer/artist Jay Gunn

October

  • Death Sentence by writer Monty Nero and artist Mike Dowling (2000AD, Rex Royd)
name: Titan Comics

description:
Brewhouse Comics is the ultimate DIY publishing house. Founded in 2012 by Josh S. Henaman, Brewhouse takes its name from the public houses of old, where the emphasis was on good drink, good company and great stories. Focusing on craft, Brewhouse aims to take that philosophy into the comic book world one story at a time. So kick back and enjoy!

Their first published volume is Bigfoot: Sword of the Earthman. In which where a dying planet needed a hero... what they got was a sasquatch.
